Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the use of coding techniques to improve the performance of multiple beamforming, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of beamforming in wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of communications and networking. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper proposes a decoding technique based on Sphere Decoding to reduce the complexity of Maximum Likelihood decoding, which is a signal processing technique. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with improving the performance of wireless communication systems, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new decoding technique to reduce the complexity of Maximum Likelihood decoding, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures.
